        		<p>Nicely written article. I grew up with a know-it-all engineer father who once told me among other bits of gospel, that it was physically impossible to design and build a soaring aircraft that was lighter than its payload. That was in 1971 and I have been hang gliding ever since, in spite of its impossibility. </p>
