			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4396" class="comment c8 c-y2010 c-m08 c-d29 c-h16 alt depth-1">
    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d19d6bb1b0945d6a8d426b7b6ecbdc23?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Miki</span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted August 29, 2010 at 17:16 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-4396" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>An absolutely wonderful article. I love it when people persevere in the face of strong criticism to realize what they are certain can be done.<br />
We sure do need more people to step in the footsteps (or rather the glide path) of the Wright Brothers and show the world what can be done.<br />
Please keep up the good work and be sure I&#8217;ll be checking back on you guys to see if you&#8217;ve broken any new records <img src='http://kimballlivingston.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':-)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>Here&#8217;s one for you. I&#8217;m sure the King and the Wright Brothers would both agree.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SBmAPYkPeYU" rel="nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SBmAPYkPeYU</a></p>
    		</div>
			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4959" class="comment c9 c-y2010 c-m11 c-d08 c-h03 depth-1">
    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fc76b43b7e2f18e6ac3abde792dde8b2?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Kris</span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted November 8, 2010 at 03:39 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-4959" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>Hey There,</p>
<p>Cool technology. How do you test for wind speed? You mention up and dwon drafts as well as oscillation&#8230;how do you know that an updraft is not catching the blades?</p>
<p>Kris.</p>
    		</div>
			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4961" class="comment c10 c-y2010 c-m11 c-d08 c-h08 alt depth-1">
    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/79803764712f27198f876273b622ee08?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">Danny Baptista</span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted November 8, 2010 at 08:53 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-4961" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>Didn&#8217;t Arthur Clarke say that if someone with great experience in an area unequivocally proclaims that something is impossible, they are probably wrong.</p>
    		</div>
			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4963" class="comment c11 c-y2010 c-m11 c-d08 c-h11 depth-1">
    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6191846a1314f2bad90e858a55cfe6e5?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n"><a href='http://www.rationalrevolution.net' rel='external nofollow' class='url url'>rationalrevolution</a></span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted November 8, 2010 at 11:44 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-4963" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>Technically, isn&#8217;t sailing downwind faster than the wind the same thing as sailing into the wind? How does the propeller continue to rotate in the same direction?</p>
    		</div>
			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4964" class="comment c12 c-y2010 c-m11 c-d08 c-h12 alt depth-1">
    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e6378b9b173dcb71306e2fed2e060285?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n"><a href='http://technicaldebt.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url url'>Jon Kern</a></span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted November 8, 2010 at 12:52 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-4964" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>As Hans von Ohain once told me, after I had asked if he worked for Junkers Jumo jet engine company:</p>
<p>&#8220;Heavens no. I worked for Heinkel, who always wanted his airplanes to go faster. Had I worked within the conventional aircraft engine world, it is doubtful that I would have been allowed to innovate with such crazy ideas as a gas turbine.&#8221; (Of course, I paraphrase to the best of my recollection.)</p>
<p>Kudos to breaking with tradition and innovating in the face of the &#8220;experts.&#8221;</p>
    		</div>
			</li>
    	<li id="comment-4969" class="comment c13 c-y2010 c-m11 c-d08 c-h15 depth-1">
